reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Worst Tissue I've Ever Used
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these tissues because the normal brand I buy was out of stock. These are the worst tissues I have ever used. They are very harsh on the skin. They are tiny. Did I mention that they are very harsh on the skin? Yeah. I will never purchase anything but Kleenex brand again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Functional, but not soft
reviews.reviewText: This tissue paper is very useable. It's for someone that blows their nose and throws the tissue away. Don't save it like the name brands! It's small and similar in texture to the tissue that hospital patients find in their rooms. Functional, yes. Soft and comfortable for your nose, no. It can quickly tear while doing its job. Regardless, I may order more unless Puffs, Scott, or Kleenex tissues get more affordable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Photo Pretty Boxes/Lousy Tissues/Sore Nose
reviews.reviewText: The tissues in these boxes are less than half the size of a regular tissue, very rough on the skin, and too thin to be useful for nose blowing. I already have a sore nose after just using two boxes. The actual boxes do NOT look like the ones in website photo which shows gleaming, gold bricks in an artistic arrangement. In reality they are just various browns, mauve, dull yellow and white which do not shine like in the photo. The boxes are also somewhat crumpled. But even if the boxes were the beautiful gleaming gold like the photo it would not matter. The tissues are the lowest quality and the worst I've ever used. I regret buying these tissues. Don't be fooled by the photo!!

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars BANG FOR YOUR BUCK
reviews.reviewText: Can't say anything special as it's a good fit for our clinic. Cheaper than some of the alternatives and considering the use, not a bad option. Will buy again, but will say shipping the products and the condition that they come in man does USPS or UPS or whoever is used to deliver really does a number. Majority of boxes dented. However, for our use, that's really not to much of a concern. Just letting others know of shipping results. Then again, I guess that's to be expected now days.
